trans-unit.source: Provides common functionality across communication protocols for generating classes for Web services.

The abstract <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class and its concrete derived classes generate client proxy code or abstract server code according to a specified communication protocol.
<xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> provides common functionality regardless of the protocol.
Within a given protocol, a concrete derived class generates a class for each supported binding defined in a Web Services Description Language (WSDL) document.

Typically, instead of directly invoking classes derived from <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter>, a developer uses these classes indirectly through the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionImporter> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter"></xref> class.
Gets the abstract XML schemas used by the associated <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionImporter"></xref> instance.
The abstract XML schemas used by the associated <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionImporter"></xref> instance

For each unhandled extension or XML element in the input extensions collection, turns on a <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionImportWarnings.RequiredExtensionsIgnored"></xref> or <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionImportWarnings.OptionalExtensionsIgnored"></xref> warning for each unhandled extension or XML element in the input extensions collection.
This method also adds the warning messages to a collection of code comments.
A <xref href="System.CodeDom.CodeCommentStatementCollection"></xref> that specifies the collection of code comments to which each warning message is added.

A <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.ServiceDescriptionFormatExtensionCollection"></xref> that specifies the extensions or XML elements for which warnings should be generated if they are not handled.
When overridden in a derived class, initializes the generation of a binding class.

When generating a class for a given binding, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.BeginClass%2A>method before generating methods that correspond to operations.
The generated class.

When generating code, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.BeginNamespace%2A> method before generating classes that represent bindings.

When overridden in a derived class, processes a binding class.

When generating a class for a given binding, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.EndClass%2A> method after generating methods that correspond to operations.
When overridden in a derived class, performs processing for an entire namespace.

When generating code, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.EndNamespace%2A> method after generating classes that represent bindings.
When overridden in a derived class, generates method code for binding classes.

When generating code, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.GenerateMethod%2A> method for each binding class method that represents an operation.
The generated method.
Gets the Web Services Description Language (WSDL) input message for the abstract operation that the protocol importer is currently processing to generate a method in a binding class.
The Web Services Description Language (WSDL) input message for the abstract operation that the protocol importer is currently processing to generate a method in a binding class.
When overridden in a derived class, determines whether a class can be generated for the current binding.

When generating code, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.IsBindingSupported%2A> method to determine whether to generate a class for the current binding, as represented by the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.Binding%2A> property.
True if the binding is supported; otherwise false.
When overridden in a derived class, determines whether the current operation's operation flow is supported.

When generating code, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.IsOperationFlowSupported%2A> method to determine whether to generate a method for the current operation, as represented by the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.Operation%2A> property.
This evaluation takes place for each operation in a binding for which a class is being generated.

If a `false` value is returned, the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter> class calls its <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.ProtocolImporter.UnsupportedOperationWarning%2A> method.
For more information, see the <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.OperationMessageCollection.Flow%2A> property.
The <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.Operation.Messages%2A> property is of type <xref:System.Web.Services.Description.OperationMessageCollection>.
An <xref href="System.Web.Services.Description.OperationFlow"></xref> enumeration value that represents a transmission pattern.
True if the current operation's operation flow is supported.
